Reesair | General Travel Site (Full Stack)

Reesair is a full-stack general travel site, a replica of TripAdvisor, fully responsive and named REESAIR. Users can view listings (hotels, cottages, etc.), add reviews, and authenticated users can manage their own listings with full CRUD operations.

---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Features

Public Users:

View all listings (hotels, cottages, etc.)

Give reviews on listings

Authenticated Users:

Signup / Login

Add new listings (hotels, cottages, etc.)

Edit or delete their own listings

Delete reviews on their listings

Access control ensures users cannot edit/delete others' listings

---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Security & Storage:

Authentication & Authorization using JWT

Cloud storage via Cloudinary for images

MongoDB used for storing other data

---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Tech Stack

Frontend: HTML, CSS, JavaScript, React, Axios, SweetAlert, React Icons, Bootstrap, Bootstrap Icons

Backend: Node.js, Express.js, Mongoose, CORS, express-fileupload, Nodemon

Database: MongoDB

Cloud Storage: Cloudinary

Tools: MongoDB Compass, Postman

---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Create a .env file inside the folder with the following:

TOKEN_KEY
DB_URL
CLOUDINARY_CLOUD_NAME
CLOUDINARY_API_KEY
CLOUDINARY_API_SECRET

---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Install dependencies:

npm install


Start server:

npm start

---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Security & Configuration

.env is added to .gitignore to keep credentials secure

Cloudinary is used for storing images securely

No sensitive information is stored in the repository

